A traffic officer linked to an illegal licensing scheme has been arrested in De Aar in the Northern Cape. CAPE TOWN - A traffic officer linked to an illegal licensing scheme has been arrested in De Aar in the Northern Cape.The 47-year-old is allegedly connected to 33-year-old Elton Abrahams, who was arrested in Belhar earlier this month.Abrahams is accused of producing illegal roadworthy certificates.Investigators seized about R3.7 million in cash when they arrested Abrahams.The Hawks' anti-corruption unit says the traffic officer arrested in De Aar on Wednesday is expected to appear in the Bellville Magistrates Court on Friday alongside Abrahams to face charges involving fraud and corruption.The unit says investigations continue and the scope affects several provinces.More arrests are expected.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)